---
---

<section
  class="hero-section relative overflow-hidden"
  aria-label="Josef Anolin — Stand-Up Comedian"
>
  <h1 class="sr-only">
    Josef Anolin — Stand-Up Comedian
  </h1>

  <div class="hero-top">
    <div class="hero-comp">
      <img
        src="/joe-hero.png"
        alt=""
        aria-hidden="true"
        class="hero-portrait select-none pointer-events-none"
      />
      <img
        src="/joe-logo.png"
        alt="Josef Anolin — Stand Up Comedian"
        class="hero-logo select-none pointer-events-none"
      />
    </div>
    <a href="#contact" class="hero-cta">BOOK ME</a>
  </div>

  <p class="hero-bio">
    From Oakland, California currently living in Los Angeles, Josef has opened
    for the likes of Tom Segura, Whitney Cummings, and Michael Che. He likes
    telling irreverent stories based on his life and observations. He has an
    Android phone because he likes pissing you off with his green text bubbles.
  </p>
</section>

<style>
  .hero-section {
    background: #000;
    height: 100%;
    /* Targets: 200px from window-top to subject's hat, 250px guard at the
       bottom. Locked to those exact values at typical desktop heights
       (1080+); shrinks proportionally on shorter viewports so the comp +
       button + bio always fit. */
    padding-top: clamp(120px, 20dvh, 200px);
    padding-bottom: clamp(160px, 25dvh, 250px);
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    padding-right: 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .hero-top {
    position: relative;
    /* Cap width by viewport height so comp + button + bio + the 200/250
       padding all fit within 100dvh. Reserve ~280px for button + gaps + bio
       beneath the comp; remaining height = comp height; width = height*1.3. */
    width: min(85%, 900px, calc((100dvh - 650px) * 1.3));
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .hero-comp {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    /* Portrait sits flush to comp top (so portrait-hat top = comp top =
       section padding-top = 200px from window). Aspect-ratio keeps the
       layered comp scaling as one unit. */
    aspect-ratio: 1.3 / 1;
  }

  .hero-portrait {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    right: 4%;
    width: 42%;
    height: auto;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .hero-logo {
    position: absolute;
    /* Logo top sits below the face — overlaps the shoulder/chest area. */
    top: 32%;
    left: 6%;
    /* Was 70%; ~30% smaller per spec. */
    width: 50%;
    height: auto;
    z-index: 2;
  }

  .hero-cta {
    /* Logo spans left:6% to 56% of comp width — its center is at 31%.
       margin-left:31% + translateX(-50%) anchors the button's center to
       the logo's center, so "BOOK ME" sits centered under the title. */
    margin-top: 1rem;
    margin-left: 31%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    background: var(--color-accent);
    color: #000;
    font-family: var(--font-display), system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    padding: 0.85rem 1.9rem;
    border-radius: 9999px;
    text-decoration: none;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    transition: filter 0.18s ease, transform 0.18s ease;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .hero-cta:hover {
    filter: brightness(1.1);
    transform: translateX(-50%) translateY(-2px);
  }

  .hero-bio {
    max-width: 60ch;
    text-align: center;
    color: rgb(229 229 229);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .hero-section { padding-left: 1rem; padding-right: 1rem; }
    .hero-top { width: 92%; }
    .hero-bio { font-size: 0.85rem; }
  }
</style>
